{
    "word": "Truce",
    "definitions": [
        "A suspension of arms by agreement of the commanders of opposing forces; a temporary cessation of hostilities, for negotiation or other purpose; an armistice.",
        "Hence, intermission of action, pain, or contest; temporary cessation; short quiet."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "Where he may likeliest find Truce to his restless thoughts."
    ],
    "etymology": "[OE. trewes, triwes, treowes, pl. of trewe a truce, properly, pledge of fidelity, truth, AS. tre fidelity, faith, troth. See True.]"
}